<leg:level id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="part" searchtype="LEGISLATION PART" subdoc="false" toc-caption="PART 2 ADMINISTRATION [rr 1&#x2013;4]">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="PART-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2" type="ext"/>PART 2</designum></desig><title searchtype="PART-TITLE">ADMINISTRATION [rr 1&#x2013;4]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[DCR Pt 2 r 1] r 1 Sittings of the Court">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R1" type="ext"/>[DCR Pt 2 r 1]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Sittings of the Court</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>1</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The registrar for a proclaimed place shall, one month before the day appointed for the commencement of a sitting of the Court at that proclaimed place, or such lesser time before that day as the circumstances permit, affix in some conspicuous place in his office a notice of the day and hour so appointed, and whenever any such day or hour is altered shall immediately affix notice of the alteration in the same place.</text></p>
<glp:note>
<p><text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF" type="legref"><ci:content>cf DCR r 2</ci:content></ci:cite></text></p></glp:note>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R1.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_DC.SGM_UCPN.DC.PT2.R1-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[DCR Pt 2 r 1.5] Court times"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.DC.PT2.R1-5" type="ext"/>[DCR Pt 2 r 1.5] </edpnum><title>Court times</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Generally speaking, matters listed for hearing commence at 10.00 am while matters in the reserve hearing list are called over at 9.30 am. If a time earlier than 10 am is appointed in respect of a hearing, care should be taken to ensure that litigants and the profession know about it: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000671" spanref="cr000671-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="NSWR"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1964"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="199"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Lynn v Ringwood</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000671-001" status="unval">[1964] NSWR 199</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="76353" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>. The Court Registry is open from 9.30 am to 4.00 pm on each business day.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_DC.SGM_UCPN.DC.PT2.R1-10" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[DCR Pt 2 r 1.10] Motions"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.DC.PT2.R1-10" type="ext"/>[DCR Pt 2 r 1.10] </edpnum><title>Motions</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Notices of motion are generally made returnable on a Friday at 9.30 am. A registrar of the Court sits from 9 am to deal with matters by consent and practitioners wishing to deal with consent matters expeditiously should appear before the Registrar from 9 am to 9.30 am for that purpose. From 9.30 am the registrar conducts a call-over of the motions remaining in the list to ascertain whether there is any reason for priority (eg, country witnesses etc); an estimate of the time required to hear the motion; and whether or not the matter has a substantive hearing pending. The remaining Motions are then referred either to the Judicial Registrar or, depending upon availability, to a Judge of the Court. Motions with an estimated hearing time of 2 hours or more are generally unsuitable to be dealt with in a Firday Motions list and will be given a date for hearing before a Judge at some future time.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[DCR Pt 2 r 2] r 2 Vacation">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R2" type="ext"/>[DCR Pt 2 r 2]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Vacation</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>2</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R2.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R2.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The Chief Judge shall appoint in each year periods to be called vacation, and one of those periods shall be called summer vacation.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am Gaz 93 of 14 June 1985  p 2632 ; Gaz 122 of 30 August 1985  p 4617]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R2.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R2.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>During vacation the Court shall sit on such days only, and for the hearing of proceedings of such types only, as the Chief Judge shall direct.</text></p>
<glp:note>
<p><text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF" type="legref"><ci:content>cf SCR Pt 2 r 5(2)</ci:content></ci:cite></text></p></glp:note>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R2.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_DC.SGM_UCPN.DC.PT2.R2-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[DCR Pt 2 r 2.5] Vacation sittings"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.DC.PT2.R2-5" type="ext"/>[DCR Pt 2 r 2.5] </edpnum><title>Vacation sittings</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>As a general rule, the Sydney District Court does not sit between the Monday before Christmas until mid January. From that time, some cases are heard but the Court does not resume sitting in a full capacity until either the last Monday in January, or the first Monday in February. If the Court is not sitting, or is only sitting in a limited capacity, urgent actions or Notices of Motion may still be listed for hearing by arrangement with the registrar.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_DC.SGM_UCPN.DC.PT2.R2-10" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[DCR Pt 2 r 2.10] Running of time"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.DC.PT2.R2-10" type="ext"/>[DCR Pt 2 r 2.10] </edpnum><title>Running of time</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Time does not stop running during vacation and accordingly default judgment may be signed during vacation.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.DC.DCRN.PT2.R3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[DCR Pt 2 r 3] r 3 Court holiday">
